EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to animals; revising provisions governing the
seizure of animals under certain circumstances; revising
certain penalties and remedies for acts of animal cruelty;
revising certain provisions governing the ownership and
care of animals treated cruelly; revising provisions
relating to immunity from civil liability for certain actions
taken to protect or remove a pet from a motor vehicle
under certain circumstances; and providing other matters
properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law requires certain officers to: (1) take possession of an animal which
2 is being treated cruelly and provide the animal with shelter and care or, with the
3 permission of the owner, humanely destroy the animal; and (2) give to the owner a
4 notice containing certain information. (NRS 574.055) Section 3 of this bill also
5 authorizes an officer that takes possession of an animal to destroy the animal in a
6 humane manner if: (1) the officer obtains an order from a court; or (2) a licensed
7 veterinarian, veterinarian technician or euthanasia technician examines the animal
8 and recommends that the animal be humanely destroyed.
9 Upon proof that proper notice has been given, existing law authorizes a court of
10 competent jurisdiction to order the animal sold at auction, humanely destroyed or
11 continued in the care of the officer. (NRS 574.055) Section 3 removes the
12 authorization for a court to order the animal sold at auction.
